        <div class="accordion-body">
          <strong>Simple & Effective Skincare Routine for Oily Skin</strong> 
          <br> Managing oily skin is all about balance—stripping it leads to more oil, while the right products help control shine and prevent breakouts without over-drying. <br>

          In the morning, start with a gentle foaming cleanser like CeraVe Foaming Cleanser or La Roche-Posay Effaclar Gel. Use a toner if needed (like The Ordinary Glycolic Acid or Paula’s Choice Pore-Reducing Toner), then apply a niacinamide serum to regulate oil and minimize pores. Follow with a lightweight, oil-free moisturizer—Neutrogena Hydro Boost or CeraVe PM are great choices. Finish with a non-greasy SPF like EltaMD UV Clear or La Roche-Posay Anthelios.
          <br>
          At night, repeat your cleanse and apply a BHA exfoliant like Paula’s Choice 2% BHA Liquid a few times a week to clear pores. For acne-prone skin, consider a treatment like Differin Gel. Seal it in with your oil-free moisturizer.
          Once or twice a week, use a clay mask like Aztec Secret for deep cleansing. And for mid-day shine, blotting sheets are your best friend.
          Keep it simple and consistent, and your skin will thank you—with fewer breakouts, less shine, and a healthy, balanced glow.
          
        </div>
