          <strong>Nourishing Skincare Routine for Dry Skin</strong> <br>
          Dry skin needs moisture and barrier support, not harsh stripping products. A few hydrating layers can go a long way in keeping your skin soft, smooth, and glowing.

          In the morning, use a gentle, creamy cleanser like CeraVe Hydrating Cleanser or La Roche-Posay Toleriane. Follow with a hydrating toner or essence—Hada Labo Gokujyun Lotion is a great pick. Add a hyaluronic acid serum for deep hydration, then seal it all in with a rich moisturizer like First Aid Beauty Ultra Repair Cream. Finish with a moisturizing sunscreen such as EltaMD UV Daily.
          
          At night, repeat your cleanse, toner, and serum. Add a face oil like squalane for extra nourishment before using a thicker night cream or balm like Weleda Skin Food or CeraVe Healing Ointment.
          
          Once or twice a week, use a hydrating mask or gentle exfoliant to smooth dry patches. With consistency, your skin will stay hydrated, healthy, and happy.
