          <strong>Balanced Skincare Routine for Combination Skin</strong> <br>
          Combination skin means you're oily in some areas (usually the T-zone) and dry or normal in others. The key is balance—hydrating without clogging and controlling oil without over-drying.

In the morning, start with a gentle gel cleanser like La Roche-Posay Toleriane Purifying Cleanser to remove excess oil without stripping dry areas. Follow with a lightweight hydrating toner or essence—Klairs Supple Preparation Toner works well. Apply a serum with niacinamide (The Ordinary Niacinamide 10% + Zinc) to help balance oil and refine pores. Use a gel-cream moisturizer like Neutrogena Hydro Boost, and finish with a non-greasy sunscreen like EltaMD UV Clear.

At night, cleanse again and repeat your toner and serum. You can spot-treat oilier areas with a BHA like Paula’s Choice 2% BHA Liquid a few times a week. Use a slightly richer moisturizer or layer a hydrating serum underneath your gel cream for drier areas.

Once or twice a week, use a clay mask on your T-zone and a hydrating mask on your cheeks to treat both zones separately. Keeping things lightweight, layered, and consistent is the best way to keep your skin clear, smooth, and balanced.
